# OVERVIEW:

Lawn tennis, commonly known as tennis, is a popular racket sport\
played between two (singles) or four (doubles) players on a\
rectangular court divided by a net. The game can be played on\
various surfaces, including grass, clay, and hard courts.

# EVENT STRUCTURE:

- Participants can participate in singles as well as doubles\
  tournaments.
- The number of knockout rounds will be decided as per the\
  number of participants.

# RULES AND REGULATIONS:

- The tournament will be conducted as per **ITF** rules.
- Further regulations regarding the game will be explained to the participants at the time of the event.
- The participation fee for individual participation is Rs\
  60.
- **Winners will be rewarded with attractive prizes.**
- NOTE: Participants are supposed to bring their own\
  lawn tennis rackets.

